whole_object: In this office, the computers have Windows but seem to have missed the view.
single_object:
- Computers: The computers in the office were "processing" the weekend couldn't come faster.
- Desks: The desk was noted by peers as "out-standing" in its field of holding up paperwork.
- Chairs: The office chairs, staging a "sit-in," were ready to roll out their demands for more ergonomic features.
- Bookshelf: The bookshelf was positively "shelf-assured," always keeping the stories in line.
- Window: The window, ever the "pane" in the glass, never failed to reflect on the brighter side of things.
- Papers: Each sheet on the desk was part of a "ream" team, ready to cover every story.
- Bulletin board: The bulletin board considered itself quite "tack-ful," always sticking to important matters.
- Trash bin: The trash bin felt it was misunderstood, but it wasn't just full of garbage; it held a lot of "basket" cases.
